theorem interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  classical
  -- First, apply the existing lemma to `Aᶜ`.
  have h :
      closure (A : Set X) = (interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ))ᶜ := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using
      (Topology.closure_compl_eq_compl_interior
          (X := X) (A := ((A : Set X)ᶜ)))
  -- Taking complements of both sides yields the desired equality.
  have h' : (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ = interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
    congrArg Set.compl h
  simpa [Set.compl_compl] using h'.symm

theorem Set.compl_compl {α : Type*} (s : Set α) : sᶜᶜ = (s : Set α) := by
  ext x
  simp
